Rating: 3
Simple yet great pasta dish - comfort food! I have made it several times and it never fails to please - even young/picky children love it. The directions are very vague though and you definitely need to double the sauce if using 1 lb of pasta. Here is my method: I like to use a mix of very ripe (almost mushy) cherry and roma/plum tomatoes; follow directions as stated but drizzle 2nd 1/3 of olive oil over tomato/crumb mixture just before putting dish in the oven. When done, stir well to break up tomatoes and incorporate the crumb/cheese mixture, then add the basil. Drain the cooked pasta and mix in final 1/3 olive oil. Add tomato sauce to pasta and mix well. If sauce seems too thick or not enough, add a little milk/light cream OR chicken/vegetable broth until you like the consistency. Serve with more grated parmesan, sit back, enjoy and revel in the sighs/smiles of your contented fellow diners!

