Rating: 2
I had some trouble with this recipe. Part of it was the gaps in the directions (what about the other 2/3 of the oil? what do you do with the sauce when it comes out of the oven? how do you combine it with the pasta?), and the other part was probably that my tomatoes weren't ripe enough. I thought they were ripe, but they probably need to be on the verge of squishiness for this recipe to work. Also, this looks like a lot of oil but do not try to skimp. I did and the pasta came out so dry, I ended up having to go back and add the extra oil at the end. If I make this again I probably will smush up the tomatoes when they come out of the oven to release some liquid. To use the oil, I would mix some of it into the breadcrumb mixture, drizzle some on top before baking, and/or add it to the finished dish before serving. I'm surprised this was chosen as a best recipe of the year. It's whimsical, but it doesn't work very well as written.

